text: Voronezh () is an Russian city, not far from Ukraine. It is the administrative center of Voronezh Oblast. It is located on the river Voronezh. The city was founded in 1586. In 2017, the city had an estimated population of 1,039,801 people. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website of Voronezh Category:Capitals of oblasts of Russia
